A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Cameroon]] on 20 May 1972. The new constitution would make the country a unitary state, as opposed to the previous federal system, as well as giving more powers to President [[Ahmadou Ahidjo]].<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/cm.html Elections in Cameroon] African Elections Database</ref> It was passed by 99.99% of voters with a 98.2% turnout.
