'''Legitimate defense of honor''' ({{lang-pt|Legítima defesa da honra}}) is a legal term in Brazilian jurisprudence, used by the defense to justify the defendant's acts as crimes of passion, attributing the motivating factor of the crime to the behavior of the victim. This justification has been used, among other reasons, to eliminate or reduce the culpability of a spouse or lover who has committed violence against a female partner.<ref>{{cite web|URL=http://revistaepoca.globo.com/Epoca/0,6993,EPT673863-1664.html|title=Defesa ilegítima|author=Paloma Cotes |date=9 February 2004|publisher=[[Época (Brazilian magazine)|Época]] |language=Portuguese |access-date=20 November 2013}}</ref><ref>[http://www.pagu.unicamp.br/sites/www.ifch.unicamp.br.pagu/files/colenc.04.a04.pdf “Legítima Defesa da Honra” - Ilegítima impunidade de assassinos. Um estudo crítico da legislação e jurisprudência da América Latina. - Autoras: Silvia Pimentel, Valéria Pandjiarjian e Juliana Belloque.]</ref>
